Hi, I have been reading a lot about this but want your advice. I have
used credit cards to pay for school and school expenses over the years
accruing rather high balances near the limits--it was an awful idea and
I would never do it again--but I am where I am now so I have to deal
with it.

I can payoff my balances in 4-5 years and no longer use or want credit
cards, but I do know that, if paid down and on time, keeping them open
will help my credit score. I really have no use for them anymore and do
not even want them, except for maybe one I have from my credit union.

Should I close all of them, even though they have balances? I have
already done this on a Chase card because they tried to jack up the
rate to ~%30. All I can say is it felt great.

Thanks for your advice!

</POST>



