&gt;Should I close all of them, even though they have balances? I have

"/> I believe that you *CAN'T* close them when they have balances, most
of the time, unless you are prepared to pay off the balance or
transfer it elsewhere or just take a HUGE black mark and refuse to
pay. And they'll look like they are open on your credit report
anyway.

Having a lot of available credit, relative to your income, is BAD
on a credit report. Having a card that's been open for a while is
GOOD on a credit report (closing your oldest cards may not be a
good idea for the credit score). Having a lot of cards or too few
cards is BAD on a credit report (whatever that means. I've heard
some guesses that 2-3 general (not specific store) credit cards is
about right).

After you get your balances down, you need to trade off the above
issues and see what you want to do.

Gordon L. Burditt

</POST>



